subsection.p:
With this new information, we can now solve initial value problems such as
y' & = -y + u_3(t) y(0) & = 2.
Notice that we can rewrite the equation y' = -y + u_3(t) as y' = \begin{cases} -y & t \lt 3 \\ -y + 1 & t \geq 3. \end{cases}

statement.p:
Find the solution of the initial value problem
2 y'' + y' + 2y = g(t) y(0) = y'(0) = 0
where g(t) is defined by g(t) = u_5(t) - u_{20}(t) = \begin{cases} 1, & 5 \leq t \lt 20, \\ 0, & 0 \leq t \lt 5 \text{ and } t \geq 20. \end{cases}
